title <size:18>Top-K Most Frequently Played Songs API (Annotated for Interview)</size>\n<size:11>Trace: "User plays a song. Play count incremented. Query: give me top 10 songs this week, globally, sorted by plays."</size>


' ====================================================================
'  STEP 1: FACADE
' ====================================================================
class MusicAnalyticsService <<Facade>> {
    - playTracker : PlayTracker
    - topKEngine : TopKEngine
    - songRepository : SongRepository
    - cacheManager : CacheManager
    --
    + recordPlay(userId, songId) : void
    + getTopKSongs(k, timeWindow) : List<SongPlayCount>
    + getTopKSongs(k, timeWindow, genre) : List<SongPlayCount>
    + getTopKSongsForUser(userId, k) : List<SongPlayCount>
    + getPlayCount(songId) : long
    + getPlayCount(songId, timeWindow) : long
    + getTrendingSongs(k) : List<SongPlayCount>
}

note top of MusicAnalyticsService #BBDEFB
    **STEP 1 - Start here.**
    "Two operations: (1) recordPlay() — called
    every time a user plays a song.
    (2) getTopKSongs(k, timeWindow) — return
    the k most played songs in a window.
    **Facade** hides tracker, ranking engine,
    cache, and data store."
    **Pattern: Facade | SRP, DIP**
end note


' ====================================================================
'  STEP 2: SONG MODEL
' ====================================================================
class Song {
    - songId : String
    - title : String
    - artist : String
    - album : String
    - genre : Genre
    - durationSeconds : int
    - releaseDate : LocalDate
    --
    + getTitle() : String
    + getArtist() : String
    + getGenre() : Genre
}

enum Genre {
    POP
    ROCK
    HIP_HOP
    CLASSICAL
    JAZZ
    ELECTRONIC
    COUNTRY
    BOLLYWOOD
}

class SongPlayCount {
    - song : Song
    - playCount : long
    - rank : int
    --
    + getSong() : Song
    + getPlayCount() : long
    + getRank() : int
}

enum TimeWindow {
    LAST_HOUR
    LAST_24_HOURS
    LAST_7_DAYS
    LAST_30_DAYS
    ALL_TIME
}

note top of Song #C8E6C9
    **STEP 2 - Core models.**
    "**Song**: id, title, artist, genre.
    **SongPlayCount**: the result object — pairs
    a Song with its play count and rank.
    **TimeWindow**: the query scope (hour/day/
    week/month/all-time)."
end note

SongPlayCount --> Song : for >
Song --> Genre


' ====================================================================
'  STEP 3: PLAY EVENT + TRACKER
' ====================================================================
class PlayEvent {
    - eventId : String
    - userId : String
    - songId : String
    - timestamp : LocalDateTime
    - source : PlaySource
}

enum PlaySource {
    SEARCH
    PLAYLIST
    RECOMMENDATION
    RADIO
    SHARED_LINK
}

class PlayTracker {
    - eventStore : PlayEventStore
    - frequencyCounter : FrequencyCounter
    - observers : List<PlayEventObserver>
    --
    + recordPlay(userId, songId) : void
    + getPlayCount(songId, from, to) : long
    + getPlaysInWindow(songId, window) : long
    - notifyObservers(event) : void
}

interface PlayEventStore <<Repository>> {
    + store(event) : void
    + getEvents(songId, from, to) : List<PlayEvent>
    + getEventCount(songId, from, to) : long
}

class InMemoryEventStore {
    - events : List<PlayEvent>
    --
    + store(event) : void
    + getEvents(songId, from, to) : List<PlayEvent>
    + getEventCount(songId, from, to) : long
}

class DatabaseEventStore {
    - connection : Connection
    --
    + store(event) : void
    + getEvents(songId, from, to) : List<PlayEvent>
    + getEventCount(songId, from, to) : long
}

note top of PlayTracker #C8E6C9
    **STEP 3 - Every play is recorded.**
    "User plays a song. PlayTracker creates a
    PlayEvent (who, what, when, from where)
    and stores it via **PlayEventStore**."

    "**Repository Pattern**: InMemory for tests,
    Database for production. Tracker also
    updates FrequencyCounter (real-time counts)
    and notifies observers."
    **Pattern: Repository | DIP, OCP**
end note

PlayEvent --> PlaySource
PlayTracker --> PlayEventStore : stores via >
PlayEventStore <|.. InMemoryEventStore
PlayEventStore <|.. DatabaseEventStore
PlayTracker --> PlayEvent : creates >
MusicAnalyticsService --> PlayTracker


' ====================================================================
'  STEP 4: FREQUENCY COUNTER — The Data Structure (KEY)
' ====================================================================
interface FrequencyCounter <<Strategy>> {
    + increment(songId) : void
    + getCount(songId) : long
    + getTopK(k) : List<SongFrequency>
    + reset() : void
}

class HashMapCounter {
    - counts : Map<String, Long>
    --
    + increment(songId) : void
    + getCount(songId) : long
    + getTopK(k) : List<SongFrequency>
    + reset() : void
}

class MinHeapCounter {
    - counts : Map<String, Long>
    - minHeap : PriorityQueue<SongFrequency>
    - heapCapacity : int
    --
    + increment(songId) : void
    + getCount(songId) : long
    + getTopK(k) : List<SongFrequency>
    + reset() : void
}

class CountMinSketchCounter {
    - sketch : int[][]
    - hashFunctions : List<HashFunction>
    - topK : MinHeap
    --
    + increment(songId) : void
    + getCount(songId) : long
    + getTopK(k) : List<SongFrequency>
    + reset() : void
}

class SongFrequency {
    - songId : String
    - count : long
}

note bottom of FrequencyCounter #FFE0B2
    **STEP 4 - The core data structure. (KEY STEP)**
    "How to count plays and get top-K efficiently?
    **Strategy Pattern** — algorithm is pluggable."

    "**HashMapCounter**: O(1) increment, O(n log k) topK.
    Simple. Works for < 100K songs.

    **MinHeapCounter**: maintains a min-heap of size k.
    O(log k) per increment. TopK is O(k).
    Best for real-time top-K with bounded memory.

    **CountMinSketchCounter**: probabilistic.
    O(1) increment, sub-linear memory.
    For millions of songs with ~1% error tolerance."

    "**This is the interview differentiator.**
    Discuss time/space tradeoffs here."
    **Pattern: Strategy | OCP, DIP**
end note

FrequencyCounter <|.. HashMapCounter
FrequencyCounter <|.. MinHeapCounter
FrequencyCounter <|.. CountMinSketchCounter
FrequencyCounter --> SongFrequency : returns >
PlayTracker --> FrequencyCounter : updates >


' ====================================================================
'  STEP 5: TOP-K ENGINE — Time-Windowed Ranking
' ====================================================================
class TopKEngine {
    - windowCounters : Map<TimeWindow, FrequencyCounter>
    - songRepository : SongRepository
    --
    + getTopK(k, window) : List<SongPlayCount>
    + getTopK(k, window, genre) : List<SongPlayCount>
    + refreshWindow(window) : void
}

class WindowRotator {
    - rotationIntervalMs : long
    - currentWindow : FrequencyCounter
    - previousWindow : FrequencyCounter
    --
    + rotate() : void
    + getCurrentCounter() : FrequencyCounter
    + getMergedCount(songId) : long
}

note bottom of TopKEngine #FFE0B2
    **STEP 5 - Time-windowed top-K.**
    "getTopK(10, LAST_24_HOURS) must only count
    plays from the last 24 hours."

    "**TopKEngine** maintains separate counters
    per TimeWindow. **WindowRotator** manages
    sliding windows: rotates every hour,
    merges current + previous for overlap."

    "For genre filtering: post-filter top-K
    results or maintain per-genre counters."
end note

TopKEngine --> FrequencyCounter : per window >
TopKEngine --> WindowRotator : rotates >
TopKEngine --> SongPlayCount : returns >
MusicAnalyticsService --> TopKEngine


' ====================================================================
'  STEP 6: SORT STRATEGY
' ====================================================================
interface SortStrategy <<Strategy>> {
    + sort(results) : List<SongPlayCount>
}

class SortByPlayCount {
    --
    + sort(results) : List<SongPlayCount>
}

class SortByTrending {
    - decayFactor : double
    --
    + sort(results) : List<SongPlayCount>
}

class SortByRecencyWeighted {
    --
    + sort(results) : List<SongPlayCount>
}

note bottom of SortStrategy #D1C4E9
    **STEP 6 - How to rank?**
    "Top-K by raw play count is simple.
    But 'trending' is different.
    **Strategy Pattern** — ranking is pluggable."

    "**SortByPlayCount**: pure frequency (default).
    **SortByTrending**: recent plays weighted more
    (exponential decay — a song played 100x
    today beats 200x last week).
    **SortByRecencyWeighted**: factors in release date."
    **Pattern: Strategy | OCP**
end note

SortStrategy <|.. SortByPlayCount
SortStrategy <|.. SortByTrending
SortStrategy <|.. SortByRecencyWeighted
TopKEngine --> SortStrategy : ranks with >


' ====================================================================
'  STEP 7: CACHE — Decorator Pattern
' ====================================================================
class CacheManager {
    - cache : Map<CacheKey, CachedResult>
    - ttlSeconds : int
    - evictionPolicy : CacheEvictionPolicy
    --
    + get(key) : CachedResult
    + put(key, result) : void
    + invalidate(key) : void
    + invalidateAll() : void
}

class CacheKey {
    - k : int
    - timeWindow : TimeWindow
    - genre : Genre
    --
    + hashCode() : int
    + equals(other) : boolean
}

class CachedResult {
    - results : List<SongPlayCount>
    - cachedAt : LocalDateTime
    - ttl : int
    --
    + isExpired() : boolean
}

interface CacheEvictionPolicy <<Strategy>> {
    + evict(cache) : void
}

class LRUCacheEviction {
    + evict(cache) : void
}

class TTLCacheEviction {
    + evict(cache) : void
}

note bottom of CacheManager #B2EBF2
    **STEP 7 - Cache hot queries.**
    "getTopK(10, LAST_24_HOURS) is called
    millions of times. Same result for seconds."

    "CacheManager caches by (k, window, genre).
    TTL-based: refresh every 60 seconds.
    **Strategy** for eviction: LRU or TTL-based."

    "On recordPlay(), selective cache
    invalidation. Stale data acceptable
    for non-critical dashboards."
    **Pattern: Strategy | SRP**
end note

CacheManager --> CacheKey
CacheManager --> CachedResult
CacheEvictionPolicy <|.. LRUCacheEviction
CacheEvictionPolicy <|.. TTLCacheEviction
CacheManager --> CacheEvictionPolicy : delegates >
MusicAnalyticsService --> CacheManager


' ====================================================================
'  STEP 8: OBSERVER — React to Play Events
' ====================================================================
interface PlayEventObserver <<Observer>> {
    + onPlayEvent(event) : void
}

class TopKRefreshObserver {
    - topKEngine : TopKEngine
    --
    + onPlayEvent(event) : void
}

class UserHistoryObserver {
    --
    + onPlayEvent(event) : void
}

class CacheInvalidationObserver {
    - cacheManager : CacheManager
    --
    + onPlayEvent(event) : void
}

class AnalyticsObserver {
    --
    + onPlayEvent(event) : void
}

note bottom of PlayEventObserver #B2EBF2
    **STEP 8 - React to every play.**
    "On each recordPlay(), multiple things
    must happen. **Observer Pattern**:"

    "**TopKRefreshObserver**: updates frequency
    counter in the engine.
    **UserHistoryObserver**: adds to user's
    personal play history.
    **CacheInvalidationObserver**: invalidates
    stale cached top-K results.
    **AnalyticsObserver**: logs for ML pipeline."
    **Pattern: Observer | OCP, SRP**
end note

PlayEventObserver <|.. TopKRefreshObserver
PlayEventObserver <|.. UserHistoryObserver
PlayEventObserver <|.. CacheInvalidationObserver
PlayEventObserver <|.. AnalyticsObserver
PlayTracker --> PlayEventObserver : notifies >
TopKRefreshObserver --> TopKEngine
CacheInvalidationObserver --> CacheManager


