    + getSongs(songIds) : List<Song>
}

class DatabaseSongRepository {
    --
    + getSong(songId) : Song
    + getSongs(songIds) : List<Song>
}

SongRepository <|.. InMemorySongRepository
SongRepository <|.. DatabaseSongRepository
TopKEngine --> SongRepository : hydrates >
MusicAnalyticsService --> SongRepository


' ====================================================================
'  WRAP UP
' ====================================================================
note as WRAPUP #FFFDE7
    **WRAP UP:** "User plays a song -> PlayTracker records event, updates
    FrequencyCounter, notifies observers (**Observer**). Counter maintains
    running counts — **HashMap** for simplicity, **MinHeap** for bounded
    memory top-K, **CountMinSketch** for millions of songs (**Strategy**).
    TopKEngine manages per-window counters with rotation. Results sorted
    by play count or trending score (**Sort Strategy**). Hot queries cached
    with TTL. The core interview discussion is Step 4: time/space
    tradeoffs of the frequency counting data structure.
    5 patterns: **Facade, Strategy (x4), Repository, Observer**."
end note


